		<div class="span-9 last">	

			<h3>OpenGL <span class="alt">Game</span> Engine</h3>
			
			For my COMP 4002 <span class="alt">Real-time 3D Game Engines</span> class I created a game engine as my term project.
			
			<br><br>
			
			It has the following standard features:
			
			<br><br>
			
			<ul>
				<li><a href="http://www.opengl.org/">OpenGL</a> based rendering</li>
				<li>Nvidia <a href="http://www.nvidia.com/object/physx_new.html">PhysX</a> physics engine intergration</li>
				<li>Loads <a href="http://graphics.cs.brown.edu/games/quake/quake3.html">Quake3 .bsp Levels</a> (created with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GtkRadiant">gtkRadiant</a>)</li>
				<li>Flythrough demo mode</li>
				<li>GLSL shaders for water (reflection/refraction effects)</li>
				<li>Lightmapping (using the maps from the .bsp files)</li>
			</ul>
			
		</div>

